               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Zubdat al-tawārīkh by Ḥaydar ibn ʻAlī Ḥusaynī Rāzī
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Ellis_Persian_10-item1">
                     <author key="person_f5409">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Ḥaydar ibn ʻAlī Ḥusaynī Rāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">حيدر بن علي حسيني رازي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Zubdat al-tawārīkh</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar">زبدة التواريخ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Majma‘ al-tawārīkh</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt">مجمع التواريخ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Tārīkh-i Ḥaydarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt">تاريخ حيدري</title>
                     <note>The manuscript lacks a preface. Above the text on f1b a note in blue pencil identifies it as the Mir'at al-Adwar of of Muslih al-din Lari, incorrectly. Over this is another in black ink identifying it as the Zubdat al-Tawarikh of Haidar(-i) 'Ali Husaini Razi which appears to be correct. F1a. Signature of Ellis, and date 25.3.02 Inserted loose near the beginning is a table of contents in the hand of Ellis. The first volume of a large general history, beginning with the creation and ending with Mamliks of Egypt. Headings in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Dhikr-i ankih awwal mawjud gasht</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, p. 124.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, Suppt. pp. 20-22. Cf. I, pp. 887-8.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
